Chocolate Cake (9 inch -- 4 layer)

1 cup butter
2.5 cups sugar
4 egg
1 cup cocoa
2 cups water
2.75 cups ketchup
2 tsp baking soda
1/2 tsp baking powder
1 tsp salt


1) Preheat oven to 350 degrees
2) Sift your flour, baking soda, baking powder, and salt into a bowl and whisk together. Set aside.
3) Boil some water. Pour your 2 cups of hot water onto your cocoa and whisk until your cocoa dissolves completely. Set aside to cool slightly.
4) Cream your butter and 2.5 cups of sugar at medium speed until light and fluffy, about 8-10 minutes.
5) Add your eggs to your sugar mixture, two at a time, and blend until incorporated. Scrape down the sides as needed.
6) Add your dry ingredients alternatively with your warm cocoa mixture. Begin by adding dry, then alternate with wet. Add dry in four parts, and the wet in three.
7) Pour your batter into your desired parchment lined pans (2 9x2 pans).
8) Bake for approximately 30-45 minutes, until a toothpick comes out clean.
9) Put 1/4 cup sugar and 1/4 cup water into a sauce pan and heat until melted. (Simple Syrup). Let cool.
10) Cut off hats, and cut into layers.
11) Douse each layer of the cake with simple syrup.
12) Apply icing (seperate recipe)